                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2946a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-01T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports from Paris indicate that the cooperation between the representatives of
                    North and South China in the discussions now taking place at the Peace
                    Conference is most cordial and effective. The practical results of such
                    cooperation might well stimulate the efforts to secure similar effective
                    cooperation in China itself.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
